com.cubeia.firebase.api.service
Interface ServiceRouter

public interface ServiceRouter

This is the contract for an object which knows how to dispatch events from a particular services to either other services, or connected clients. In other words, it is the services connection with the message bus in the Firebase cluster.

A service that wishes to receive events should implement the RoutableService interface.

Author:
Larsan

void dispatchToService(ServiceDiscriminator disc,
                       ServiceAction action)
                       throws NoSuchRouteException
Sends an action to a particular service. The data will be wrapped and dispatched across the message bus asynchronously.

Parameters:
disc - The service discriminator, must not be null
action - Action to include, must not be null
Throws:

dispatchToPlayers

void dispatchToPlayers(int[] players,
                       ServiceAction action)

This method can be used to send an event to multiple players. It also functions as a general broadcast if the given player id parameter is null in which case it send the action to all logged in players.

The data will be wrapped and dispatched across the message bus asynchronously.

Parameters:
players - Players to send data to, or null for all logged in players
action - Action to send, must not be null

dispatchToGame

void dispatchToGame(int gameId,
